**Closed Loop Analytics** is a data-driven approach that integrates the full lifecycle of data—from **collection in source systems** and the pipeline that published those source application databases into a [[Domain Data Lake House]]. Through **analysis and insight generation**, to **action and feedback**, which then informs future data collection and decision-making.

It is “closed loop” because the results of analytics are **fed back into operational processes**, enabling continuous improvement, refinement of actions, and validation of outcomes. This ensures that **insights aren’t just observed—they are acted upon**, and the impact of those actions is **measured and used to inform future decisions**.

